docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/TESTING.md,project,Context evaluation workflow
body: "pm eval measures SEARCH ranking quality (nDCG/MRR golden queries, shipped via pm-u8n5/pm-22x2) but nothing measures whether pm context / pm next assemble the RIGHT working set — the core promise of 'project management = context management'. The adaptive relevance engine (pm-4k6b) will change assembly behavior; without a quality harness we cannot prove it is an improvement, tune signal weights, or catch regressions.\n\nProposal: extend the eval pattern from search to context assembly.\n- Golden workspaces: a small real-shaped snapshot plus pm-mi2x synthetic workspaces at 10k/100k scale.\n- Graded judgments: given agent state (focus item, active claim, plan step, query), the ideal context set with per-item relevance grades.\n- Rank-aware scoring (nDCG-style) over the assembled context and next ordering, plus token-budget adherence checks.\n- Phase 1 (now): baseline today's structural assembler — same before/after role pm-a22j plays for token cost.\n- Phase 2 (with pm-4k6b): per-signal attribution in eval output so weight tuning is evidence-driven; gate in CI like the search eval.\n\nSDK-first: the runner consumes only public SDK read primitives (pm-rjqr), so custom scorers from extensions are evaluable with the same harness."
